{"id": 225030206, "title": "Victoria Beckham Recalls Newspaper Highlighting Where She Needed To Lose Weight Post-Birth", "text": "The show's host, Chris Evans, shamelessly asked Victoria if her weight was \u201cback to normal\u201d two months after giving birth. When she said she was back to her pre-pregnancy weight, Chris brought out a set of scales and asked if he could \u201ccheck\u201d himself. Victoria appeared visibly uncomfortable throughout the ordeal, saying, \u201cOh no.\u201d She later added, \u201cThis is horrible,\u201d as she stepped onto the scales. Chris then proceeded to read out her exact weight to the entire audience and viewers at home.", "summary": "<h1>It comes two years after Victoria reflected on the horrific time she was forced to be weighed on live TV just two months after giving birth to her first child.</h1><p><img src=\"https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2024-05/29/10/enhanced/5250efae0be5/original-5322-1716979192-2.jpg?crop=1243:829;0,0\" /></p><hr /><p><a href=\"https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/leylamohammed/victoria-beckham-newspaper-lose-weight-post-birth-insecure\">View Entire Post &rsaquo;</a></p>", "url": "https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/leylamohammed/victoria-beckham-newspaper-lose-weight-post-birth-insecure", "image": "https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2024-05/29/13/campaign_images/034954becf8f/victoria-beckham-recalled-feeling-incredibly-inse-3-3450-1716988250-0_dblbig.jpg?resize=1200:*", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 13:10:54", "author": "https://www.buzzfeed.com/about,Leyla Mohammed", "authors": ["https://www.buzzfeed.com/about", "Leyla Mohammed"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": -0.896}